2015-05-21 13:32:21		[core]  /set  [<option> [<value>]]
2015-05-21 13:32:21		              diff [<option> [<option>...]]
2015-05-21 13:32:21		              env [<variable> [<value>]]
2015-05-21 13:32:21		set config options and environment variables
2015-05-21 13:32:21		option: name of an option (wildcard "*" is allowed)
2015-05-21 13:32:21		 value: new value for option, according to type:
2015-05-21 13:32:21		          boolean: on, off or toggle
2015-05-21 13:32:21		          integer: number, ++number or --number
2015-05-21 13:32:21		           string: any string ("" for empty string)
2015-05-21 13:32:21		            color: color name, ++number or --number
2015-05-21 13:32:21		        Note: for all types, you can use null to remove option value (undefined value). This works only for some special plugin variables.
2015-05-21 13:32:21		  diff: display only changed options
2015-05-21 13:32:21		   env: display or set an environment variable (use value "" to unset a variable)
2015-05-21 13:32:21		Examples:
2015-05-21 13:32:21		  display options about highlight:
2015-05-21 13:32:21		    /set *highlight*
2015-05-21 13:32:21		  add a word to highlight:
2015-05-21 13:32:21		    /set weechat.look.highlight "word"
2015-05-21 13:32:21		  display changed options:
2015-05-21 13:32:21		    /set diff
2015-05-21 13:32:21		  display changed options in irc plugin:
2015-05-21 13:32:21		    /set diff irc.*
2015-05-21 13:32:21		  display value of environment variable LANG:
2015-05-21 13:32:21		    /set env LANG
2015-05-21 13:32:21		  set environment variable LANG and use it:
2015-05-21 13:32:21		    /set env LANG fr_FR.UTF-8
2015-05-21 13:32:21		    /upgrade
2015-05-21 13:32:21		  unset environment variable ABC:
2015-05-21 13:32:21		    /set env ABC ""
